I"<p><a href="https://github.com/funkfinger/electronic-tests/tree/master/test_no_arduino_attiny85_i2c_lcd">This is hacked to all get out</a>, but using some sometimes modded Arduino libraries as a start and info found all over the net, I finally managed to get my ATtiny85 talking I2C to a <a href="http://www.ebay.com/sch/i.html?_odkw=i2c+lcd+2x16&amp;_osacat=0&amp;_from=R40&amp;_trksid=p2045573.m570.l1313.TR0.TRC0.H0.Xi2c+lcd+2x16+1602.TRS0&amp;_nkw=i2c+lcd+2x16+1602&amp;_sacat=0">cheap I2C LCD</a>. Why no Arduino? Because I want my own timer interrupts and the ATtiny Arduino core uses the timer(s?) I want to use for <code class="highlighter-rouge">millis()</code> stuff…</p>

<p><img src="http://media.jaywiggins.com.s3.amazonaws.com/images/attiny85%20i2c%20lcd.jpg" alt="attiny85 i2c lcd" /></p>

